put.description:
This service allows you to register an empty collection. If you have a MoDaC user account with upload permission, you can add an empty collection (Program, Study, or Asset). If an existing collection has user metadata, you can update that metadata. If an existing collection has been configured to contain another collection, you can add a collection. 


By default, this service expects the containing collection for the collection you are registering to already exist at the time of registration. However, you can optionally request that this service create the parent and higher-level collections. To do so, set the ‘createParentCollections’ indicator in the json file to true, and provide the list of metadata for the parent collections through parentCollectionsBulkMetadataEntries. In this case, this service creates the entire collection hierarchy above the registered collection.

1. **CURL COMMAND**
  ```
  curl -k -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @<attributesFile.json> -X PUT <server>/api/collection/{path} -H "Accept: application/json" -D  <response-header> -o <response-message.json> -u <Your Email Id>

  ```
  2.  **attributesFile.json Example**
  ```
     {
     "createParentCollections": true,
        "metadataEntries": [{
            "attribute": "study_identifier",
            "value": "study_1_"
          },
          {
            "attribute": "collection_type",
            "value": "Study"
          }
        ],

        "parentCollectionsBulkMetadataEntries": {
          "defaultCollectionMetadataEntries": [{
            "attribute": "collection_type",
            "value": "Folder"
          }]
        }
      }

  ```
  3. **EXAMPLE - CURL COMMAND**
  ```
  curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @collection.json -X PUT https://modac.cancer.gov/api/collection/NCI_DOE_Archive/testnew/1_18_2020 -H "Accept: application/json" -D header.txt -o output.json -u us39@nih.gov
  ```

post.description:
This service allows you to transfer a collection from MoDaC to an accessible Globus Endpoint location (asynchronous download) or AWS S3 bucket (asynchronous download). 

**When downloading a collection**:

•  the path parameter represents the logical path of the collection registered with MoDaC.

 •  provide either a Globus destination which describes the endpointt or S3 destination which includes S3 bucket and account


•  for a Globus destination, if you set the optional ‘destinationOverwrite’ indicator to ‘true’ and if the destination file exists, this service overwrites the destination file. If you omit this indicator and the destination file exists, then this service rejects the transfer request.


**Note**:  A MoDaC user account is a pre-requisite for downloading data from MoDaC. Additionally, for downloading to a Globus endpoint, you must grant write access to the service account. For details, refer to [Preparing to Use Globus](https://wiki.nci.nih.gov/display/MoDaCdoc/Preparing+to+Use+Globus) wiki page.

1. **CURL COMMAND**
 ```
 curl -k -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @<Attributes-file.json> -X POST <server>/api/v2/collection/{path}/download -H "Accept: application/json" -D  <response-header> -o <response-message.json> -u <Your Email ID>

 ```
 2.  **attributesFile.json Example**

 ```
  a. To request a download to a Globus endpoint
        { 
          "globusDownloadDestination": {
                                "destinationOverwrite" : true,
            "destinationLocation": {
              "fileContainerId": "4a3b132a-815f-11e7-8dff-2",
              "fileId": "/coll-test-2-15-2021"
            }
          }
        }

  b. To request a download to AWS S3
        { 
          "s3DownloadDestination": {
            "destinationLocation": {
              "fileContainerId": "ccbr-sbg-1",
              "fileId": "coll-many-files-12-10-18"
            },
            "account" : {
              "accessKey" : "<insert-access-key",
              "secretKey" : "<insert-secret-key",
              "region" :"us-east-2"
            }
          }
        }


 ```
 3. **EXAMPLE - CURL COMMAND**
 ```
 curl -k -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @attributesFile.json -X POST https://modac.cancer.gov/api/v2/collection/NCI_DOE_Archive/JDACS4C/JDACS4C_Pilot_1/asset_/download -H "Accept: application/json" -D header.txt -o output.json -u us39@nih.gov
 ```

put.description:
This service allows you to register a data file in a collection. If you have permissions to modify an existing collection, you can upload data to that collection if that existing collection has been configured to contain data files. 

You can upload a data file synchronoulsy (directly from your machine) or asynchronously (from Globus and AWS S3)


  For obtaining upload permission or permission to modify the metadata of a file, please contact modac-support@nih.gov



 1. **CURL COMMAND**
  ```
  A. Sync Registration 

 curl -k -F
 "dataObjectRegistration=@<attributesFile.json>;type=application/json"
 -F "dataObject=@<filePath>" -X PUT
 <server>/api/v2/dataObject/<collection path>/<dataObject Name> -u < Email ID>


 B. Async Registration

 curl -k -F "dataObjectRegistration=@globus.json;type=application/json"
 -X PUT <server>/api/v2/dataObject/<collection path>/<dataObject Name> -D
 header.txt -o output.json -u <Your Email ID>

  ```
  2.  **attributesFile.json Example**

  ```
   A. Sync Upload - attributesFile.json
         { 
           "metadataEntries": [
             {
               "attribute": "description",
               "value": "my-dataObject-description"
             },
             {
               "attribute": "my-second-attribute-name",
               "value": "my-second-attribute-value"
             }
           ]
       }

   B. Register from Globus - attributesFile.json

          {
             "globusUploadSource": {
               "sourceLocation": {
                 "fileContainerId": "16572124-19cb-11e9-934d-0e3d676669f4",
                 "fileId": "test.txt"
               }
             },
             "metadataEntries": [{
               "attribute": "description",
               "value": "Tes1"
             }, {
               "attribute": "Asset Type",
               "value": "test"
             },{
                           "attribute": "Asset_identifier",
                           "value": "test"
                   },{
                           "attribute": "Asset_name",
                           "value": "test"
                   }]
           }

   C. Register from S3 - attributesFile.json
           {
               "s3UploadSource": {
                 "sourceLocation": {
                   "fileContainerId": "s3-bucket-name",
                   "fileId": "s3-object-key"
                 },
                 "account" : {
                   "accessKey" : "aws-access-key",
                   "secretKey" : "aws-secret-key",
                   "region" :"aws-region"
                 }
               },
               "metadataEntries": [
                 {
                   "attribute": "description",
                   "value": "my-file-description"
                 }, 
                 {
                   "attribute": "my-second-attribute-name",
                   "value": "my-second-attribute-description"
                 }
               ]
             }

  ```
  3. **EXAMPLE - CURL COMMAND**

  ```
  A. Sync Registration 
  curl -k -F "dataObjectRegistration=@syncupload.json;type=application/json" -F "dataObject=@header.txt" -X PUT https://modac.cancer.gov/api/v2/dataObject/NCI_DOE_Archive/JDACS4C/JDACS4C_Pilot_1/anl_cancer_gene_expression_data/header_.txt -u us39@nih.gov

  A. Async Registration
  curl -k -F "dataObjectRegistration=@globus.json;type=application/json" -X PUT https://modac.cancer.gov/api/v2/dataObject/NCI_DOE_Archive/JDACS4C/JDACS4C_Pilot_1/anl_cancer_gene_expression_data/test_1_28_2021_globus_new.txt -D header.txt -o output.json -u us39@nih.gov
  ```

post.description:
This service allows you to transfer a data file from MoDaC to one of the following possible destinations: 



• Your machine or your file system (synchronous download) 

• Globus endpoint (asynchronous download) 

• AWS S3 (asynchronous download) 


  **When downloading a data file**:


  •  the path parameter represents the logical path of data file registered with MoDaC. 

 •  provide either a Globus destination which describes the endpointt or S3 destination which includes S3 bucket and account. 


•  for a Globus destination, if you set the optional ‘destinationOverwrite’ indicator to ‘true’ and if the destination file exists, this service overwrites the destination file. If you omit this indicator and the destination file exists, then this service rejects the transfer request.


**Note**:  A MoDaC user account is a pre-requisite for downloading data from MoDaC. Additionally, for downloading to a Globus endpoint, you must grant write access to the service account. For details, refer to [Preparing to Use Globus](https://wiki.nci.nih.gov/display/MoDaCdoc/Preparing+to+Use+Globus) wiki page.


1. **CURL COMMAND**
   ```
    curl -k -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @<attributesFile.json> -X POST <server>/api/v2/dataObject/{path:.*}/download -H "Accept: application/json" -D  <response-header> -o <response-message.json> -u <Your Email IdD>

  2.  **JSON FILE EXAMPLES**
  ``` 
  a. To request download to FileSystem

        { 
          "metadataEntries": [
            {
              "attribute": "description",
              "value": "my-dataObject-description"
            },
            {
              "attribute": "my-second-attribute-name",
              "value": "my-second-attribute-value"
            }
          ]
      }


  b. To request a download to a Globus endpoint


      "JSON:
      {
        "globusDownloadDestination": {
          "destinationLocation": {
          "fileContainerId": "4a3b132a-815f-11e7-8dff-22000b9923ef",
            "fileId": "test-2-02-21"
          },
       "destinationOverwrite" : true,
        }
      }


 c.   To request a download to Amazon S3 bucket
          {
            "s3DownloadDestination": {
              "destinationLocation": {
                "fileContainerId": "ccbr-sbg-1",
                "fileId": "demo-file-2-2-21"
              },
              "account" : {
                "accessKey" : "***",
                "secretKey" : "***",
                "region" :"us-east-1",
              },
          "destinationURL" : “https://...”
            }
          }



  ```
  3. **EXAMPLE - CURL COMMAND to download file to Globus**
  ```
  curl -k -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @attributesFile.json -X POST https://modac.cancer.gov/api/v2/dataObject/NCI_DOE_Archive/testnew/12_1_2020/Data_12_1/bulk_metadata_file2.xlsx/download -H "Accept: application/json" -D header.txt -u us39@nih.gov
  ```


  4. **EXAMPLE - CURL COMMAND to download file to s3**


  ```
  curl -k -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @aattributesFile.json -X POST https://modac.cancer.gov/api/v2/dataObject/NCI_DOE_Archive/testnew/12_1_2020/Data_12_1/bulk_metadata_file2.xlsx/download -H "Accept: application/json" -D header_S3.txt -u us39@nih.gov
  ```



  5.  **EXAMPLE - CURL COMMAND to download file to FileSystem**
  ```
  curl -k -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @attributesFile.json -X POST https://modac.cancer.gov/api/dataObject/NCI_DOE_Archive/testnew/12_1_2020/Data_12_1/bulk_metadata_file2.xlsx/download -H "Accept: application/json" -D header_local.txt -u us39@nih.gov
  ```

This API transfers a list of collections from MoDaC to another accessible Globus location or to an AWS S3 bucket. The caller provides a list of collection paths, and destination information for their Globus Endpoint or AWS3 bucket where they are looking to download the data to.  

**Note**: For Globus Download, the WRITE per **MODAC-PROD-App-Accts-Pool-NCI_DOE** permission needs to be added to your Globus endpoint. Information on how to add permission to your endpint is located in  [Preparing to Use Globus](https://wiki.nci.nih.gov/display/MoDaCdoc/Preparing+to+Use+Globus) wiki page.

An optional ‘appendPathToDownloadDestination’ indicator can be provided. If set to true, the entire object path will be used when files are created in the download destination, otherwise, just the file name will be used. By default this indicator is set to true.


1. **CURL COMMAND**
 ```
 curl -k -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @<attributesFile.json> -X POST <server>/api/v2/download -H "Accept: application/json" -D  <response-header> -o <response-message.json> -u <Your Email ID>

 ```
 2.  **attributesFile.json Example**

 ```
  a. To request a download to a Globus endpoint
        {
             "collectionPaths" : [
                 "/NCI_DOE_Archive/MoDaC_3_4/3_4_2021_identifier",
                 "/NCI_DOE_Archive/MoDaC/12_1_2020/Data_12_1"
        ],
        "globusDownloadDestination": {
                "destinationOverwrite" : true,
                  "destinationLocation": {
                      "fileContainerId": "16572124-19cb-11e9-934d-0f4",
                          "fileId": "bulk-collections-1_28_2021_2nd"
                        }
        }
        }

  b. To request a download to AWS S3
        {
          "collectionPaths": [
            "/NCI_DOE_Archive/JDACS4C/JDACS4C_Pilot_2/Test1",
            "/NCI_DOE_Archive/JDACS4C/JDACS4C_Pilot_2/Test2"
          ],
          "s3DownloadDestination": {
          "destinationLocation": {
            "fileContainerId": "ccbr-sbg-1",
            "fileId": "test-collection-bulk-download-08-17-19"
          },
          "account": {
            "accessKey": "your-access-key",
            "secretKey": "your-secret-key",
            "region": "us-east-2"
          }
        },
        "appendPathToDownloadDestination": true
      }


 ```
 3. **EXAMPLE - CURL COMMAND**
 ```
 curl -k -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @attributesFile.json -X POST https://modac.cancer.gov/api/v2/download -H "Accept: application/json" -D header.txt -o output.json -u us39@nih.gov
 ```
